#Preliminaries
library(ggplot2)
library(ggthemes)
library(patchwork)
library(TeachingDemos)
char2seed("coffee")
d <- read.csv("hw12data.csv")
str(d)
## 'data.frame':    40 obs. of  5 variables:
##  $ FG  : int  2 3 1 0 2 1 0 1 2 1 ...
##  $ Comp: Factor w/ 8 levels "C","F","FR","FRT",..: 3 4 8 1 7 6 1 8 7 2 ...
##  $ AGB : num  424 192 459 0 185 ...
##  $ BGB : num  432 190 1201 829 627 ...
##  $ RSA : num  561 329 849 793 700 ...
# First Graph
g1 <- ggplot(data=d, mapping=aes(x=FG,y=AGB)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth()
print(g1)

# Second Graph
g2 <- ggplot(data=d,
             mapping=aes(x=FG,fill=I("pink"),color=I("seagreen"))) +
  geom_bar(stat="count") +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
print(g2)

# Third Graph
g3 <- ggplot(data=d,
             mapping=aes(x=AGB,fill=I("magenta"),color=I("black"))) + geom_histogram()
print(g3)

# Fourth Graph
g4 <- ggplot(data=d,
             mapping=aes(x=Comp,y=BGB,fill=BGB)) + geom_boxplot() + geom_jitter() + theme(legend.position="none")
g4

#New Fancy Chart- This did not work the way I wanted it to, but it is a cool tool. 

g5 <- ggplot(data=d, aes(x=FG, y=AGB)) + 
  geom_point(size=3) + 
  geom_segment(aes(x=FG, 
                   xend=FG, 
                   y=0, 
                   yend=AGB)) + 
  labs(title="Lollipop Chart", 
       subtitle="FG Vs AGB", 
       caption="source: hw12data") + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65, vjust=0.6))

print(g5)

#Adding then all together
g1 + { 
  g2 + 
    g3 + 
      g4 +
       plot_layout(ncol=1)
    
  
}
